On Tue, Jul 8, 2008 at 6:17 AM, John Baker <busvwzen(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:
> Hey Y'all,
> Please look at this pic and tell me 2 things:  1)If this is indeed an alternator with Internal Voltage regulator...and 2)If so, how is this wired to the system of a 70 bus??  Terminals read D-, DF, and D+

It looks like you have an externally regulated alt, the internal AL82
has two connections, a threaded stud (B+  to battery) and a spade
connector (D+ to charge light).  I think that the regulator was
located under the back seat in the beetle.

